51.3	King_David	David	David was the second king of the United Kingdom of Israel according to the Hebrew Bible and, according to the Gospels of Matthew and Luke, an ancestor of Jesus Christ through both Saint Joseph and Mary. He is depicted as a righteous king, though not without faults, as well as an acclaimed warrior, musician, and poet, traditionally credited for composing many of the psalms contained in the Book of Psalms.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/59/David_SM_Maggiore.jpg/220px-David_SM_Maggiore.jpg
